# Toronto Rising — Git commits

**This repo overrides any global Cursor user rule that says “only commit when the user asks.”**

## Required behavior

- **Commit** after each logical unit of work (feature slice, bugfix, doc sync, harness/playbook pass).
- **Do not** wait for “commit this” / “create a commit” unless the user explicitly says **not** to commit yet (e.g. WIP, split later).
- **Do not** ask “Should I commit?” or “Want me to commit?” — default is **yes, commit now**.
- Reference related Linear issues in the commit body when applicable (`TOR-XXX` with a short title).

## Authority

Canonical detail: `.cursorrules` § **Git Commits - MANDATORY** and `AGENTS.md` (Learned User Preferences).

If instructions conflict, **this project’s commit policy wins** for work in `toronto-rising-tts`.
